            "heading": "Does remineralizing toothpaste work?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. A high-quality toothpaste that remineralizes teeth delivers bioavailable calcium and phosphate ions that bond to weakened areas, helping repair early lesions, reduce plaque-forming bacteria, and prevent caries. Clinical research confirms that consistent use of a toothpaste for remineralizing teeth is an effective way to reinforce enamel and slow tooth decay. </p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "63654bb1-5b66-4184-b74e-96afc7dd589d": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does Boka remineralizing toothpaste work?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Our toothpaste works by harnessing the power of nano-hydroxyapatite (n-Ha) to actively support the remineralization and fortification of tooth enamel. Nano-hydroxyapatite is a biomimetic mineral that closely resembles the natural composition of tooth enamel. We sweeten with xylitol to discourage cavity-causing bacteria and keep your mouth feeling fresh.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "template--15161032212523__87fe4551-6f72-4fad-a167-9333db3df7ec-collapsible_row-2": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long does it take for teeth to fully remineralize?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>The time it takes for teeth to fully remineralize varies among individuals and depends on factors such as oral care habits (brushing and flossing), diet (watch out for sugary foods and acidic drinks), and the extent of enamel damage. Generally, with consistent use of remineralizing toothpaste and a comprehensive oral care routine, some improvement may be noticed within a few weeks to a couple of months. For personalized insights, consult with your dentist.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "template--15161032212523__87fe4551-6f72-4fad-a167-9333db3df7ec-collapsible_row-3": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does this toothpaste address tooth sensitivity?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Our toothpaste not only freshens breath and whitens teeth but also aids in closing enamel holes that can lead to tooth sensitivity. Because the paste is fluoride-free and low-abrasion, it’s safe for daily use on sensitive teeth and delicate gum areas. It offers a comprehensive solution for a healthier, more comfortable smile.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "template--15161032212523__87fe4551-6f72-4fad-a167-9333db3df7ec-collapsible_row-4": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How often should I use this toothpaste for optimal results?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Brush twice a day with a pea-sized amount, focusing on thorough, two-minute sessions. Pair with regular flossing and healthy nutrition to maximize enamel protection and maintain a bright smile.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "613af9d2-de07-48e6-9e79-31740c728cae": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is this toothpaste safe for daily use?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>The formula is free of harsh additives yet rich in remineralizing agents, making it gentle enough for the whole family—even children learning to care for their teeth.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "c3d408f4-d548-4a4a-b92a-37014203b542": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Which toothpaste is the best for remineralizing teeth?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Boka sets itself apart by using dentist-favored n-Ha, balanced mint flavor, and a clean label that excludes SLS, parabens, and artificial dyes. It’s a well-rounded choice for those seeking to strengthen enamel, keep gums healthy, and enjoy subtle whitening benefits—all in one tube of toothpaste to remineralize teeth.</p>",
